Cataract surgery, being the most common application of ophthalmic knives, is driving substantial demand for these instruments. The rising prevalence of cataracts, particularly among the elderly population, is fueling the need for advanced ophthalmic knives that can deliver optimal surgical outcomes. In addition, the increasing incidence of glaucoma and the growing demand for refractive surgery are further driving the market for ophthalmic knives. Surgical procedures such as trabeculectomy and corneal surgery require specialized knives to address the specific needs of patients suffering from these conditions.

Hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, and specialty clinics constitute key end users in the ophthalmic knives market. Hospitals, with their advanced infrastructure and skilled healthcare professionals, account for a significant share of the market owing to the high volume of eye surgeries performed in hospital settings. Ambulatory surgical centers are gaining traction due to their cost-effectiveness, quick turnaround times, and patient-centric approach. These centers offer a convenient alternative for patients undergoing ophthalmic procedures, contributing to the overall market growth.

